Review: Early scenes of specialized social language, defamiliarized references, conversations only meaningful if arbitrarily invested in—interesting. Freak NYC theater-goers laugh because they hear the words they know. The rest maybe amounts to an awkward character study. It is for the moment unclear to me why ambiguity is a virtue in itself. Just wanted to hear nice music.
